The paper discusses deep learning for supervised learning, specifically in computer vision related tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper mentions pseudo-ensembling-based approaches, which are commonly used in computer vision tasks and fall under the category of cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses domain constraint, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the paper mentions simulations, which suggests the use of neural networks (cs.NE).
